RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': 'Based on the trace analysis results, I can see a clear pattern of errors. The trace_analysis_tool shows that the dominant issue is "Error 9001 (HY000): PD server timeout: start timestamp may fall behind safe point" occurring in the productcatalogservice with very high occurrence counts (431, 315, 311 times across different pods). This error is also propagating to the frontend service, causing HTTP 500 errors.\n\nThe status_combinations data clearly shows this PD server timeout error as the most frequent issue, appearing 431+ times in the productcatalogservice and propagating to frontend services. This error message indicates a database-related issue with PD (Placement Driver) server timeout, which is likely related to TiDB or a similar distributed database system. The "safe point" reference suggests this is a timestamp-based consistency issue in the database layer.\n\nWhile there are also some payment service connection errors visible in the raw traces, the overwhelming majority of errors (by count) are the PD server timeout errors affecting the product catalog service.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_trace_keys": ["error_ratio", "frontend->productcatalogservice", "PD server timeout", "HTTP status code: 500"],\n  "affected_components": ["productcatalogservice", "frontend"],\n  "missing_traces": [],\n  "trace_summary": "Product catalog service experiencing \'Error 9001 (HY000): PD server timeout: start timestamp may fall behind safe point\' with 431+ occurrences, causing HTTP 500 errors in frontend service. This indicates a database-level issue with the Placement Driver (PD) server in the distributed database system used by productcatalogservice.",\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_database_status",\n    "reason": "PD server timeout errors indicate database infrastructure issues",\n    "suggested_metrics": ["pd_server_uptime", "tidb_safe_point_lag", "database_connection_pool"],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["PD server", "safe point", "timestamp", "productcatalogservice"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
